{
  "text": "The geometry-free ionosphere-free linear combination, i.e. wide-lane carrier-phase minus narrow-lane code [CITATION_1] , provides direct access to the wide-lane ambiguities. However it still contains the receiver and satellite biases. The satellite phase biases are obtained from the RTX network processor system [CITATION_2] . The remaining biases are obtained by combining the divergence-free phase combination and the code measurement [CITATION_3] . The ionospheric phase combination and ionospheric code combination are employed to estimate the ionosphere delay to each satellite. At this point the ionosphere delays, the wide-lane ambiguities and the phase biases are known and/or derived, and only the modelling of the tropospheric delay remains. The total tropospheric delay can be represented by",
  "citation_candidates": [
